==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inkhorn
<hw>Ink"horn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ink</ets> +
<ets>horn</ets>; cf. F. <ets>cornet ⟦agrave⟧ encre</ets>, G.
<ets>dintenhorn</ets>.]</ety> <def>A small bottle of horn or other
material formerly used for holding ink; an inkstand; a portable case for
writing materials.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧With a writer's <xex>inkhorn</xex> by
his side.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ezek. ix. 2.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From his pocket the notary drew his papers and
<qex>inkhorn</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inkhorn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inkhorn
<hw>Ink"horn"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Learned; pedantic;
